  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**CART (Gini) vs C4.5 (Entropy):**  \n",
    "- **Gini** measures class impurity — computationally cheaper, slight preference for balanced splits.  \n",
    "- **Entropy** measures information content; C4.5 uses gain ratio, reducing bias toward high-cardinality features.  \n",
    "- Compare the tree diagrams: the root feature and split thresholds often differ between criteria.  \n",
    "- In practice on tabular data, performance differences are small. The **cost-adjusted variant** of either algorithm typically delivers better business value.\n"
   ]
  },
